  "text": "Cerebral blood flow was measured using a bolus-tracking method that requires an intravenous bolus injection of ICG ͑0.1 mg/ kg͒, followed by continuous measurements of the time-varying concentrations of ICG in arterial blood and brain tissue. [CITATION_1] The arterial concentration c a ͑t͒ was measured by a dye densitogram ͑model DDG-2001 A/K, Nihon Kohden, Tokyo, Japan͒, and the brain tissue concentration c icg ͑t͒, was measured by NIRS. The two concentration curves are related by the following equation:",
